channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: WATCH: Judge Explains Dismissal in Alec Baldwin Case; See the Barnburner Reactions.
Yearslong tensions boil over as ex-Obama staffers gang up on Biden: 'Clooney was exactly right'
item.description: The tensions between President Biden and former President Obama go back nearly two decades and are once again in the spotlight as the former faces calls to end his re-election bid.

item.title: Carville Pushes Biden to Withdraw or 'Lose the Constitution'
item.description: Democrat operative James Carville doubled down on his call for President Joe Biden to exit his presidential campaign. "If the people don't want you to win, you're not going to win," Carville said on a podcast this week. "And they clearly don't ...

item.title: Feel-Good Friday: A Young Man With a Learning Disability Overcomes It, and Now Runs His Own Business
Congressional bypass: Many Democrats elusive on Biden issue
item.description: While some Congressional Democrats have called on Biden to step aside, others have shared opaque statements, deflected or avoided responding to questions about the president altogether.

item.title: WashPost: Biden in 'Denial' About His Political 'Frailty'
item.description: The Washington Post editorial board wrote that President Joe Biden remains in "denial" about his personal and political "frailty," adding he's "somewhat oblivious" to the unrest enveloping him in the aftermath of the debate and fresh "cringeworthy" stumbles on Thursday.

item.title: Meta Suddenly Eases Guardrails on Trump Facebook/Instagram Accounts to Protect 'Political Expression'
White House doctor pressured to convince Biden to take cognitive exam, publicize results
item.description: Sen. Lindsey Graham pleaded with the White House doctor to convince Biden he should take a new neurological exam and make the results public.

item.title: Rep. Lawler to Newsmax: 'New York Coming Into Play' for Trump
item.description: Rep. Mike Lawler, R-N.Y., told Newsmax on Friday that "there's no question that New York is coming into play" for former President Donald Trump. President Joe Biden won New York state by 23 points in 2020 but currently leads Trump by only 8.

item.title: Ragin' Cajun Carville: Keeping Biden in Race Is 'Exactly What Donald Trump Wants Us to Do'
Lawmakers rip Army brass over training slides suggesting pro-life groups could be tied to terrorism
item.description: At least 25 Republicans called on Army Secretary Christine Wormuth to explain slides used in training at Fort Bragg/Fort Liberty depicting pro-life groups among potential terror threats.

item.title: Trump to Biden: Let's Take a Cognitive Test
item.description: On Friday, former President Donald Trump called on President Joe Biden to join him in taking a cognitive test.

item.title: Bungling Biden Gets Cold Shoulder From Dems at MI Event, Descends to Lying, Sniffing, and Other Weirdness
Biden campaign hypes president's foreign policy chops after high-stakes NATO press conference
item.description: The Biden campaign is praising the president's performance during Thursday's NATO press conference despite strong pushback from Republicans and the Trump campaign.

item.title: Dems Use Panic Over Biden as Fundraising Pitch
item.description: Down-ballot Democrat candidates are adopting a new election strategy: monetize panic. The campaign of Rep. Josh Harder, D-Calif., launched a fundraising email with the subject line "I'm concerned," according to a copy obtained by Axios.
